ZURICH, Switzerland, October 31  – Former president of the Ghana Football Association (GFA) Kwesi Nyantakyi was banned for life from football for bribery and corruption by Fifa on Tuesday.
Fifa’s Ethics Committee found Nyantakyi guilty of other charges including conflict of interest.
In addition to his life ban, Nyantakyi was fined 500 000 Swiss Francs (R7.28m). (ANA)